{
  "stem": "9899.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So it was not an easy deed to suddenly surround us all and carter us off someplace.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in 1941, my sister was born.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was born on September 15.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And by that time, the Germans had already taken over a very old part of the town and decided that that would be the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The ghetto is a place where they put a certain type of people to live in misery and poverty.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in this way, they control what they do, if they go out, if they go in.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They can number them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were able to put names to each person and identify them to their use and to their advantage.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when my-- the ghetto was opened at the end of August, and slowly they were carting-- sending everybody else there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The day my sister was born-- and as it was customary in those times, the better class of people had their babies at home.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would not go to a hospital.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my sister-- my mother delivered my sister in her bed in our house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And a few hours later, there was a knock on the door.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the Germans appeared and told us that we had 24 hours to leave and go to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My mother was distraught, because she was supposed to stay in bed at least a month.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they would not give her-- they would deny her that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They-- they wanted her to go right away, but my father begged them to have mercy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And instead of just shooting us on the spot, somehow they decided that 24 hours would be-- would be appropriate.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in the meantime, they proceeded to devastate the whole house.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
